         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">5/9/77. ¶  ¶ The Grevillea, sent by you, dear Mr Jephcott, is Grevillea ericifolia of Robert Brown. The Lobelia-like plant is Isotoma axillaris of Lindley, ¶  and — as you observed — it is more powerf...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">77.09.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edwin Jephcott</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5/9/77.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Grevillea, sent by you, dear Mr Jephcott, is <name key="Grevillea%20ericifolia">Grevillea ericifolia</name> of Robert Brown. The Lobelia-like plant is <name key="Isotoma%20axillaris">Isotoma axillaris</name> of Lindley,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">R. Brown (1830). p. 20; Lindley (as 'J. L') in Edwards (1815-28), vol. 12, t. 964.</p>
               </note> and — as you observed — it is more powerful even than L. inflata, indeed very poisonous even in a small dose. The work on the "plants of Victoria" is still in manuscript, as my Department is almost ruined, and I have no means of getting it printed and the woodcuts done.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">B79.13.08?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I examined twice the Mount Coskiusko<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Mt Kosciusko, NSW.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> range, in 1854 from the Maneroo-side,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Monaro, NSW. </seg>M's spelling was common at that time. For M's response to this first trip see B55.11.01.</p>
               </note> and 2 years ago from Mr Finlay's place.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M visited the upper Murray River region and the neighbouring mountains in January 1874; see M to J. Francis, 27 January 1874 (in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>74-01-27a) and M to G. Bentham, 27 January 1874.</p>
               </note> I had however to go up from the South East side of the Range, and never examined the north west portion, which is nearer to Walwa.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Vic.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I took horses straight on to the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">North part</hi>
               </seg>, from Mr Watsons could one climb the range there on foot? and could I get any help in the district, so that I could camp out for a night with one or two companions?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have not prospered after 30 years toil in Australia, and find that these journeys are too costly for my sole means. Among the granit hills is also much yet to be discovered as regards plants there, as I examined only the one near Mr Watsons and lost the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">spring</hi>
               </seg> vegetation. Try with your young son to make a good &amp; full collection now of all the spring-plants there, including those of the rivers &amp; <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">lagoons</hi>
               </seg> &amp; swamps!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Amongst the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">minutest</hi>
               </seg> plants would be most novelty.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I found several plants, <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new</hi>
               </seg> to science on the granit mountains near you, but did not get the flowers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Grevillea%20ericifolia">Grevillea ericifolia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Isotoma%20axillaris">Isotoma axillaris</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Lobelia%20inflata">Lobelia inflata</name>
            </p>
         </div>
